post_text: Thank you to Mr. Araujo for sharing this great project! Students at Old Kings Elementary School are putting their own twist on spreading positivity. The school has started the “OKES Shells” project where students decorate a seashell then write a positive message on it and place it in the school’s courtyard for other students to read. So next time you are on campus keep a lookout for “OKES Shells”.

post_text: Every 10 years, the @uscensusbureau undertakes a mammoth task: counting all the people residing in the United States. This count affects the allocation of funding for our community’s public resources (e.g., roads, hospitals, schools), how we plan for the future, and our voice in government. Learn more about the importance of the #2020Census and how to participate: https://buff.ly/2HS74x5.

post_text:
Flagler Schools was proud to have incoming Superintendent Cathy Mittelstadt on the dais for the first time, taking part in Tuesday afternoon's School Board workshop.

The School Board also recognized Superintendent James Tager for his three years of service to the District. He retires June 30th.

Also recognized were Hunter Perez and Shelcey Garcia, our Student School Board Members. Although Shelcey was unable to attend the meeting, the Board hopes to honor her in person later this month.
